Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Remove the @21 Day Aged British Sirloin Steaks{2} and @unsalted butter{30%g} from your fridge to allow them to come up to room temperature.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over the @peri peri seasoning{1%sachet}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, pick the @mint{1%bunch} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

Pick the @thyme{1/2%bunch} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a garlic press).

Once the butter has softened slightly, pop into a small #bowl{} and add the garlic and thyme.

Use a #fork{} to mash it all together. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then keep to one side.

Once the chips have cooked for about 15 mins, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Season the steaks with salt and pepper.

Once hot, lay the steaks into the pan and fry until browned, ~{1%minute} on each side.

Lower the heat slightly and cook for another ~{1-2%minutes} on each side if you want them medium-rare.

> TIP: Cook for 1-2 mins more if you like it more well done.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. The steak is safe to eat when browned on the outside.

Once cooked, transfer to #plate{} and spread over the garlic thyme butter. Cover with #foil{} and allow to rest for a couple of mins.

Meanwhile, wipe out (now empty) the frying pan and pop it back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{} (no need to clean).

Once hot, add the @peas{120%g} and @chilli flakes{1%pinch} (use less if you'd prefer things milder). Stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from the heat, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then stir through the mint.

When everything's ready, slice the steaks into 1cm thick slices and transfer to your #plates{}. Spoon over any melted butter from the resting plates.

Serve with the peri peri chips and peas alongside. Enjoy!